<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-17310] locking the offline dir can destroy the broker exceptionally</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17310</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17176&quot; title=&quot;Move FileLock to server-common module&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-17176&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-17176&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; migrated the FileLock to java, and all `IOException` is wrapped by `RuntimeException`. However, LogManager only handles the `IOException` so the the `RuntimeException` will escape from error-catch and then destroy the broker.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/5d66f8d88cc3121236287157a2d46856dbae4512/core/src/main/scala/kafka/log/LogManager.scala#L273&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/5d66f8d88cc3121236287157a2d46856dbae4512/core/src/main/scala/kafka/log/LogManager.scala#L273&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
